1	Acetazolamide	carbonic anhydrase inhibitor,diuretic,glaucoma,epilepsy	Acetazolamide is a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor used primarily to treat glaucoma, epilepsy (as an adjunct), and altitude sickness. It also acts as a diuretic to reduce fluid retention and is sometimes used for periodic paralysis and idiopathic intracranial hypertension.
